    <value>
      <type>Rule</type>
      <data>&quot;Definition of test type interaction&quot;
[&quot;cellular example&quot;]
__&lt;Test_type&gt;interacts_with__&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object,other_test_object) whenever
    big_extent&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) contains little_extent&lt;Test_type&gt; 
                                                 (other_test_object) and 
    test_object != other_test_object and owned_object&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) != 
                                         null
;
</data>
    </value>
    <value>
      <type>Rule</type>
      <data>&quot;Increment count of meetings&quot;
[&quot;cellular example&quot;]
when __&lt;Test_type&gt;interacts_with__&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object,other_test_object) becomes true
    if meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) = null then
        set meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) = 0
    fi ;
    set meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) = meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; 
                                                 (test_object) + 1
;
</data>
    </value>
    <value>
      <type>Rule</type>
      <data>&quot;Decrement count of meetings&quot;
[&quot;cellular example&quot;]
when __&lt;Test_type&gt;interacts_with__&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object,other_test_object) becomes false
    if meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) &gt; 0 then
        set meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) = meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; 
                                                     (test_object) - 1
    fi ;
    if meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) = 0 then
        set meeting_count&lt;Test_type&gt; (test_object) = null
    fi
;
</data>
